    {
        "user": "UCUSW7WVD",
        "type": "message",
        "ts": "1720629178.815819",
        "edited": {
            "user": "UCUSW7WVD",
            "ts": "1720629240.000000"
        },
        "client_msg_id": "e16421b1-15f2-49c7-a9f1-2900fb871227",
        "text": "To respond to <@UC2A2ARPT>'s comment above:\n\n> In general, I love the idea of \"we build the thing we want\". I just don't know that anyone here with the skills to do that has the time and interest in doing it for free.\nI've spent some time introspecting, and I think I do have the time and interest to do this for free, at least to see where it leads. But I definitely don't have all the skills. But maybe a few of us could put our heads together?\n\nOne big thing missing is design\/aesthetics. I don't know and worse have no idea what it takes to get to a level of polish that would retain Ivan or <@U5STGTB3J>.\n\nSeeing others bring up the problem of dependencies makes me feel like I'd be building for the right people. I'd probably run out of steam pretty quickly working on Zulip or even Slack if it was open source. On the other hand, building something that is both polished and parsimonious in its dependencies feels like breaking new ground rather than following well-understood steps. Might be hard to build something usable quickly.\n\nI'm curious what others think.",
        "team": "T5TCAFTA9",
        "user_team": "T5TCAFTA9",
        "source_team": "T5TCAFTA9",
        "user_profile": {
            "avatar_hash": "6e649a383cf8",
            "image_72": "https:\/\/avatars.slack-edge.com\/2019-07-14\/687915485201_6e649a383cf8f9e366e3_72.png",
            "first_name": "Kartik",
            "real_name": "Kartik Agaram",
            "display_name": "",
            "team": "T5TCAFTA9",
            "name": "ak",
            "is_restricted": false,
            "is_ultra_restricted": false
        },
        "thread_ts": "1720065086.549499",
        "parent_user_id": "UC2A2ARPT",
        "blocks": [
            {
                "type": "rich_text",
                "block_id": "XNut8",
                "elements": [
                    {
                        "type": "rich_text_section",
                        "elements": [
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": "To respond to "
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "user",
                                "user_id": "UC2A2ARPT"
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": "'s comment above:\n\n"
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "rich_text_quote",
                        "elements": [
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": "In general, I love the idea of \"we build the thing we want\". I just don't know that anyone here with the skills to do that has the time and interest in doing it for free."
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "rich_text_section",
                        "elements": [
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": "\nI've spent some time introspecting, and I think I do have the time and interest to do this for free, at least to see where it leads. But I definitely don't have all the skills. But maybe a few of us could put our heads together?\n\nOne big thing missing is design\/aesthetics. I don't know and worse have no idea what it takes to get to a level of polish that would retain Ivan or "
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "user",
                                "user_id": "U5STGTB3J"
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": ".\n\nSeeing others bring up the problem of dependencies makes me feel like I'd be building for the right people. I'd probably run out of steam pretty quickly working on Zulip or even Slack if it was open source. On the other hand, building something that is both polished and parsimonious in its dependencies feels like breaking new ground rather than following well-understood steps. Might be hard to build something usable quickly.\n\nI'm curious what others think."
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                ]
            }
        ]
