    {
        "user": "UC2A2ARPT",
        "type": "message",
        "ts": "1720630939.268269",
        "client_msg_id": "5ab4ebc8-8f65-4b9a-a8f9-5264f4618f83",
        "text": "Most of these design points I find quite appealing, in particular:\n\n&gt; • Markdown input\n&gt; • Make threads independent of category =&gt; enable trivial moving of posts\n&gt; • As little bespoke HTML as possible, minimize use of custom classes\n&gt; • No mandatory client-side javascript, and no javascript at all—as far as possible\n&gt; • Move slow\n&gt; • Minimize maintenance requirements through minimizing external infra and dependencies; <https:\/\/cblgh.org\/password-restoration|eschew email>\nWe've seen with the projects you (Kartik) and Mariano have done that there's interest in producing other frontends for the \"database\" of posts made by the community. I feel like, with the right technical choices, that could be made a lot easier and more fun.\n\nLike, the \"no mandatory client-side javascript\" is a very client-centric view. If someone wanted a SPA \/ PWA client, or realtime updates, or notifications, or whatever… that shouldn't be a hard thing to do.\n\nBy building something that offered a great \"bring your own client\" experience, we could encourage people to test out \/ share their novel FoC tools by building a client (or some other piece).",
        "team": "T5TCAFTA9",
        "user_team": "T5TCAFTA9",
        "source_team": "T5TCAFTA9",
        "user_profile": {
            "avatar_hash": "gf94d2ed5e18",
            "image_72": "https:\/\/secure.gravatar.com\/avatar\/6f94d2ed5e188be9865a531021b0afcd.jpg?s=72&d=https%3A%2F%2Fa.slack-edge.com%2Fdf10d%2Fimg%2Favatars%2Fava_0013-72.png",
            "first_name": "Ivan",
            "real_name": "Ivan Reese",
            "display_name": "Ivan Reese",
            "team": "T5TCAFTA9",
            "name": "ivanreese",
            "is_restricted": false,
            "is_ultra_restricted": false
        },
        "thread_ts": "1720065086.549499",
        "parent_user_id": "UC2A2ARPT",
        "blocks": [
            {
                "type": "rich_text",
                "block_id": "Q\/8dF",
                "elements": [
                    {
                        "type": "rich_text_section",
                        "elements": [
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": "Most of these design points I find quite appealing, in particular:\n\n"
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "rich_text_list",
                        "elements": [
                            {
                                "type": "rich_text_section",
                                "elements": [
                                    {
                                        "type": "text",
                                        "text": "Markdown input"
                                    }
                                ]
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "rich_text_section",
                                "elements": [
                                    {
                                        "type": "text",
                                        "text": "Make threads independent of category => enable trivial moving of posts"
                                    }
                                ]
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "rich_text_section",
                                "elements": [
                                    {
                                        "type": "text",
                                        "text": "As little bespoke HTML as possible, minimize use of custom classes"
                                    }
                                ]
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "rich_text_section",
                                "elements": [
                                    {
                                        "type": "text",
                                        "text": "No mandatory client-side javascript, and no javascript at all—as far as possible"
                                    }
                                ]
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "rich_text_section",
                                "elements": [
                                    {
                                        "type": "text",
                                        "text": "Move slow"
                                    }
                                ]
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "rich_text_section",
                                "elements": [
                                    {
                                        "type": "text",
                                        "text": "Minimize maintenance requirements through minimizing external infra and dependencies; "
                                    },
                                    {
                                        "type": "link",
                                        "url": "https:\/\/cblgh.org\/password-restoration",
                                        "text": "eschew email"
                                    }
                                ]
                            }
                        ],
                        "style": "bullet",
                        "indent": 0,
                        "border": 1
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "rich_text_section",
                        "elements": [
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": "\nWe've seen with the projects you (Kartik) and Mariano have done that there's interest in producing other frontends for the \"database\" of posts made by the community. I feel like, with the right technical choices, that could be made a lot easier and more fun.\n\nLike, the \"no mandatory client-side javascript\" is a very client-centric view. If someone wanted a SPA \/ PWA client, or realtime updates, or notifications, or whatever… that shouldn't be a hard thing to do.\n\nBy building something that offered a great \"bring your own client\" experience, we could encourage people to test out \/ share their novel FoC tools by building a client (or some other piece)."
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                ]
            }
        ],
